Hey <@U0153M0K2N7> I've used both Mixpanel & GA for website conversion tracking at my previous organization (Automate IO). 

You can create events in Mixpanel like button clicks, form submit, product signup etc., and create a funnel out of it to track the conversion rate. 

Other than that, you can create a custom segments using filters and trigger them with notifications using Mixpanel. 

But if you're only looking for website events tracking, then you can set up GA events which will work fine.

elements.text:
I've used both Mixpanel & GA for website conversion tracking at my previous organization (Automate IO). 

You can create events in Mixpanel like button clicks, form submit, product signup etc., and create a funnel out of it to track the conversion rate. 

Other than that, you can create a custom segments using filters and trigger them with notifications using Mixpanel. 

But if you're only looking for website events tracking, then you can set up GA events which will work fine.
